Closing arguments in the bail application for two men accused of murdering farm manager Brendin Horner, resume in the Senekal Magistrates Court today. Editor's note: This livestream has ended. You can watch the recording above. JOHANNESBURG - The Senekal Magistrates Court in the Free State heard closing arguments in the bail application of two men accused of killing farm manager Brendin Horner. The matter is postponed to Thursday 22 October for judgment on the bail application. The appearance of Sekwetje Mahlamba and Sekola Matlaletsa has been overshadowed by drama outside the court. READ:Â Senekal calm ahead of Bredin Horner murder case Last week, AfriForum and EFF held protests outside court with a heavy police presence.